The paper discusses the design of a fair prediction model using logistic regression, which is a popular machine learning algorithm for classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of game theory and adversarial perspectives, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper addresses fairness in decision making, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
